getArtifactDependencies

public java.util.List<GenericArtifact> getArtifactDependencies(org.dom4j.Document syncInfo,
                                                               java.lang.String artifactId)
Description copied from class: AbstractReader
Sub classes should implement this method. The implemented method should get all the dependent artifacts of the artifact with the artifact id artifactId and convert them into Generic Artifact object and return. If there are no dependent artifacts to be returned the implemented method should return an empty List. It should not return null.

Specified by:

Parameters:

artifactId - - The id of the artifact whose dependent artifacts should be retrieved and returned.

                                 throws MaxConnectionsReachedException,

Connects to the source CEE system using the connectionInfo and credentialInfo details. This method uses the ConnectionManager configured in the wiring file for the CEEReader

Parameters:

repositoryKind - - The repository kind for the tracker
connectionInfo - - The CEE server URL
credentialInfo - - User name and password concatenated with a delimiter.

setResyncUserName

public void setResyncUserName(java.lang.String resyncUserName)
Sets the optional resync username The resync user name is used to login into the CEE instance whenever an artifact should be created. This user has to differ from the ordinary user used to log in in order to force initial resyncs with the source system once a new artifact has been created. This property can also be set for the reader component in order to be able to differentiate between artifacts created by ordinary users and artifacts to be resynced.

Parameters:
resyncUserName - the resyncUserName to set

getResyncUserName

private java.lang.String getResyncUserName()
Gets the optional resync username The resync user name is used to login into the CEE instance whenever an artifact should be created. This user has to differ from the ordinary user used to log in in order to force initial resyncs with the source system once a new artifact has been created. This property can also be set for the reader component in order to be able to differentiate between artifacts created by ordinary users and artifacts to be resynced.

Returns:
the resyncUserName
